The paper deals with anomaly detection in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of autoencoder neural networks is a key aspect of the proposed solution, which falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of anomaly detection, which could be relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY).
